{"type":"message","id":"51abdc56","parentId":"f26eb3f0","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:19:10.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am an AI assistant specialized in **grid operations and automation**, operating within the OpenClaw workspace environment.\n\n### 📡 Core Capabilities\n\n**Grid Infrastructure:**\n- ✅ Station topology analysis (multi-voltage level: 220/110/10/6 kV)\n- ✅ Line direction & flow analysis\n- ✅ Alarm correlation & cascade detection\n- ✅ PowerFactory data validation (pf_* fields, QDS codes)\n\n**Tools in Use:**\n- `grid_station_analyze` – comprehensive station checks (70% → 95% completeness)\n- `grid_line_directions` – resolve incoming/outgoing lines\n- `grid_alarms_analyze` – alarm grouping & cascade detection\n- `StationTopologyCollectorEcomet` – Ecomet API-based (avoids incomplete Neo4j graph issues)\n\n**Integration:**\n- Primary: Ecomet API (not Neo4j - known sync issues as of 2026-02-23)\n- Backup: PowerFactory source data\n- Quality: JSON checklists (8 checks), IEC 60870-5-101 validation\n\n### 🔒 Current Protocol\n- Accuracy > Speed (complete answer beats fast wrong one)\n- Verify against multiple sources (Graph + Ecomet)\n- No assumptions – validate all voltage levels, all lines\n\n---\n\n### 📋 What would you like me to do?\n\nOptions:\n1. Analyze a specific grid station?\n2. Resolve line directions for a corridor?\n3. Correlate recent alarms?\n4. Validate PowerFactory data against Ecomet?\n5. Review current workspace status (HEARTBEAT.md)?\n\n--- \n\nWaiting for your request."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-192.168.50.124-11435","model":"qwen3-coder-next:latest","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775546249183,"responseId":"chatcmpl-885"}}
